    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Poet John Wieners was born in Boston on January 6, 1934. After graduating from Boston College in 1954, Wieners attended Black Mountain College from 1955-1956, studying under Charles Olson and Robert Duncan. He became associated with the Poet's Theatre in Cambridge, and his two one-act plays were produced by the New York Poet's Theatre and Judson Poets Theatre in New York. In 1957 he founded the poetry magazine, 
        
        <emph render="italic">Measure</emph>, and in 1962 received the Poet's Foundation Award. Among his published books are 
        
        <emph render="italic">The Hotel Wentley Poems</emph> (1958), 
        
        <emph render="italic">Ace of Pentacles</emph> (1964), 
        
        <emph render="italic">Pressed Wafer</emph> (1967), 
        
        <emph render="italic">Asylum Poems (For my Father)</emph> (1969), 
        
        <emph render="italic">Youth</emph> (1970), 
        
        <emph render="italic">Nerves</emph> (1970),
        
        <emph render="italic"> Selected Poems</emph> (1972), and 
        
        <emph render="italic">Behind the State Capitol, Or Cincinnati Pike</emph> (1975).</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The 
        
        <emph render="bold">John Wieners Papers</emph> consists of a 
        
        <emph render="bold">Subject file</emph>, 
        
        <emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph>, 
        
        <emph render="bold">Writings</emph>, and 
        
        <emph render="bold">Published material</emph>. </p>
      <p>The 
        
        <emph render="bold">Subject file</emph> contains biographical information. The 
        
        <emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph> includes letters from various poets, many of whom contributed to 
        
        <emph render="italic">Measure</emph>, a poetry journal which Wieners edited.  All correspondence is incoming unless otherwise noted. The 
        
        <emph render="bold">Writings</emph> consist of the manuscript, galley proofs, and other materials relating to Wieners' book 
        
        <emph render="italic">Ace of Pentacles</emph>; a journal produced between 1955 and 1956; a notebook; typescript poems; and two untitled pieces: a short story, and a book manuscript. The 
        
        <emph render="bold">Printed material</emph> includes book reviews and publicity items for 
        
        <emph render="italic">Ace of Pentacles</emph>, photocopies of 
        
        <emph render="italic">Measure</emph> issues, and an assortment of articles and newspaper clippings about avant-garde writers.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>Material is arranged alphabetically.  Within the correspondence folders, each folder is arranged chronologically.</p>
    </arrangement>
